2011: North Korea faces another UN sanction over its latest nuclear test.
2012: Kim Jong-Il dies and is succeeded by his son Kim Jong-un.
2013: Kim Jong-un is awarded the Nobel Peace Prize and featured on the cover of Time Magazine for his accomplishment of Korean reunification.
2014: American military withdraws from the Korean Peninsula. General Motors declares bankruptcy for the second time.
2015: The effects of peak oil are felt as gas prices reach up to 20 dollars a gallon due to a war between Iran and Saudi Arabia. Russia cuts off all oil trade with Europe. Survivalist literature become bestsellers in America. China's influences diminish.
2016: America withdraws its military from Japan and other countries overseas, focusing on its instability back home. Texas splits from the United States, border bloodshed takes place as refugees from other states attempt to enter Texas.
2017: Martial law is declared in the United States as its infrastructure crumbles due to financial deficiencies.
2018: After the destruction of one of its nuclear facilities by Korean special forces, Japan surrenders to the Greater Korean Republic and is capitalized into a vassal state.
2019: The UN goes out of commission.
2020: Canada closes its borders to Americans. The US military takes over the functions of many emergency services, as well as the distribution of basic goods. This causes many Americans to abandon the suburbs in exchange of the military-managed urban centers.
2021: Korean forces succeed in annexing many countries in Southeast Asia. A new pandemic known as the Knoxville Cough, type of bird flu, begins to spread in the United States.
2022: To prevent the contagion of the Knoxville Cough, Mexico closes its borders to Americans. Hyperinflation pushes the US dollar to the edge of collapse.
2023: The Knoxville Cough ravages the American public. The Korean People's Army reaches 20 million total personnel.
2024: Using the captured M-V rockets at the Uchinoura Space Center, Kim Jong-un announces a new space satellite program, under the pretense of replacing the decaying GPS system, which America could no longer afford to maintain.
2025: A thermonuclear device is detonated by one of the Korean satellites 300 miles above Kansas, blanketing America with an EMP that wipes out its power grid and most of the electronics above ground. The economic downfall in Europe prevents its nations from intervening.
2026: The United States is split into two as the KPA irradiate the entire Mississippi River, as a fortification for their control of the western side.
2027: The United States Armed Forces are completely scattered.

Allergy sufferers suffer from a singular problem with vacuum cleaners. Several vacuum cleaners spew out airborne debris. Here is how can one single out the right one for you.

It's not exactly airborne dirt and dust. Eighty percent of home dust is essentially lifeless skin cells from our shedding skin cells and our dogs or cats, and the feces from dust mites that consume this skin dander. Most of us are not significantly influenced by this "dust", Several of us put up with sneezing, runny nose, and headaches from only a minuscule amount of this stuff hanging in the air. What has this to do with vacuum cleaners? A lot, it turns out.

Great filtration is the most important concern here. HEPA (High Efficiency Particulate Air) filters on the exhaust of practically any vacuum will help catch the tiny particles that hold everything that sets off your allergies. You will want to make sure that that the filtration system is sealed. Sealed signifies that the surrounding air is forced through the filtration system, and can't flow around the filter. HEPA filters that are not sealed are as worthless as not making use of one at all, as all the air will escape around the filter material, as it is the easiest route.  Practically all HEPA filters are made out of the exact same substance. They are made in numerous sizings and shapes, but they accomplish the same task, as long as they are in actuality sealed filters.

Very nearly no HEPA filters are washable. Some producers declare they are, however it is approximating attempting to wash down a paper plate. They deteriorate and fragment. Many HEPA filters might be cleaned, at least partially, by making use of an air compressor to blow out the filtration system. Really be sure the unclean side of the filter is directed away from you. Otherwise you can actually push the dirt and filth further into the filtration system. 

Generally HEPA filters need to be replaced one time a year. This may change extensively depending on how often you vacuum, if you own dogs or cats that shed, and how much carpet you possess. Carpet fibers traps and stores dirt and pet hair, and plus stores the dander and minuscule mites that survive on that dog and cat dander.

What is the vacuum cleaner exterior manufactured from? There are different qualities of plastic. The less expensive vacuum cleaners are created from ABS which will warp if it gets warm enough. This warping will be able to let dirt to bypass the filter system and discharge out into the room air we inhale. This really is one of the core reasons vacuum cleaners lose their air flow after many years. The motor is even in decent shape, but in reality the dirty air is leaking out into the room, escaping past the filters. The air is also being pulled in from places on the vacuum besides the nozzle on the flooring. This warping is also why you will find airborne dirt and dust gathering up on the outside of the vacuum cleaner following two or three years.

Interestingly, the motor material can help with the allergy symptoms. A metal motor in the vacuum cleaner will dissipate the heat from within the motor. A cool motor is not going to heat up the plastic casing enough to warp it. Your vacuum cleaner HEPA filter will be kept sealed and filtering the airflow. 

A charcoal filter in your vacuum cleaner will furthermore help with the vacuum cleaner filter as well as keep pet distinct odors to a minimum.

Steam cleaning  carpeting routinely, maybe once a year, will revive  a carpeted floor.  We advise making use of hot water extraction carpet cleaners. They do a more thorough job than the dry foam technique, although they could make a mess if you don't use the cleaner properly.

Bagless vacuums also might initiate an airborne allergen attack when you dump out the container. We propose using HEPA filter paper bags, or Micron Filtration bags to store the dirt and pet hair. They produce less of a grubby cloud when you get rid of them.

9vNe0O_G9OE.title: Summer NAMM 2015: Yamaha Reface CS Keyboard Demo by Sweetwater
9vNe0O_G9OE.description:
Avery from Yamaha presents the Reface CS keyboard at Summer NAMM 2015. Inspired by the iconic CS-80 polyphonic analog synthesizer, the Yamaha Reface CS mobile mini keyboard evokes the very essence of the legendary synth of yesteryear. Packed with five types of synthesis and onboard effects, the Reface CS provides you with a variety of lush pads, fat basses, and solo leads. Each type of synthesis has its own set of Texture and Mod sliders that take simple oscillator types and let you turn them into gentle soundscapes, mangled sonic carnage, and everything in between.

After the video, get the Yamaha Reface CS here: http://www.sweetwater.com/store/detail/RefaceCS

OOdKOOPZrRk.title: Blues Guitar Xtravaganza - Ron Thompson - BoomBoomBoomBoom
OOdKOOPZrRk.description:

Filmed here, at Rene Solis' October Blues Guitar Extravaganza, he offers a rare treat...his version of 'BoomBoomBoomBoom'.  As I stood there trying to get some light into the shot, he made a few funny faces for the camera and I just lost it.
What a great night. Rene--you really hit it out of the park with this show.

--MF
